Added environment.yml to clarify dependency versions used within this branch
I am using conda as an environment management and package installer system. Within my virtual environment (called MeterVEnv), i have these specific versions of dependencies utilised, because conda recognises that some of these dependencies do not play nice with each other because of transitive conflict of flask-sqlalchemy 3.1.1 → needs flask≥2.2.5 → needs werkzeug≥2.3.3, but werkzeug was locking flask to be a version earlier than 2.2.5. I'll try to force upgrade werkzeug to the stable  version 2.3.7, then flask to 2.3.2, then finally sqlalchemy to stable version 3.1.1
